Rating: 4
This is one of my all time favorite recipes. To make it more portable (like to grill at a friend's or take for a camping trip), I prepare the marinade and put it in one gallon freezer bags. You can put the veggies in the bag and just shake them to cover them well. You can actually do this in advance and let the marinade get cold. It sticks to the vegetables when it's cold, but melts again when you put it on the grill.

