Rating: 2
So many wonderful reviews, I carefully prepared the basting sauce (1/2 cup olive oil, 1/4 cup butter) with bated breath. I had to take the pan off the heat and whisk like mad, because the Dijon curdled. The shallots remained firm and never released their delicious flavor. Next time I made my own version with less trauma. In a microwaveable cup, saute 1/3 cup shallots in 1 Tbsp butter until softened. Add half cup chicken or vegetable broth. Bring to a boil. Add 2 Tbsp olive oil and 1 Tbsp butter, diced. Let cool while you chop 2 Tbsp fresh thyme in food processor (any fresh herbs work). Add 3 Tbsp Dijon mustard,1 Tbsp balsamic vinegar and 1 Tbsp fresh lemon juice to chopped thyme in food processor bowl. With motor running, through feed tube of processor, SLOWLY pour broth mixture - as if you are making hollandaise sauce - and continue processing until broth and oil are emulsified. Add lemon peel and season to taste. Brush veggies with mixture at least ten minutes before barbecuing. Delicious and much more foolproof!!

