Rating: 3
The flavors in the basting sauce are delicious with all of the vegetables, but I think the huge amount of fat added is totally unnecessary. I tried it this way: Saute the shallots in just 1 or 2 tablespoons butter until golden. Add 1/2 cup chicken or vegetable broth and the rest of sauce ingredients, skipping the rest of the butter and the olive oil. I serve the grilled vegetables over rice for a great, light meal. Cooking the vegetables inside on a broiling pan also works in a pinch. You can also use rosemary instead of thyme, or do it without herbs--it's still very tasty.

